ation in the British Numismatic Journal.","Artist":"Edward III (1327-77)","Date":"1338–1343","Medium":"coin","CreditLine":"The Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge — Coins and Medals","URL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/id/object/265862","ImageURL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/imagestore/portfolio/F25982D9_7CB9_CFFF_028E_8BBFC531887C/640/123/CM_149_2000_obv_201509_eer26_mas.JPG"},{"ObjectID":32246,"Title":"Botanical drawings","Artist":"Schouman, Aert","Date":"","Medium":"album","CreditLine":"The Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge — Paintings, Drawings and Prints","URL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/id/object/32246","ImageURL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/imagestore/pdp/pdp13/PD_127_1973.jpg"},{"ObjectID":34478,"Title":"The private pleasure of Prince Parwez, son of Jahangir by Miskin","Artist":"Unknown","Date":"1678–1698","Medium":"miniature (painting)","CreditLine":"The Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge — Paintings, Drawings and Prints","URL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/id/object/34478","ImageURL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/imagestore/portfolio/F25982D9_7CB9_CFFF_028E_8BBFC531887C/649/495/PD_205_1948_4_mas.jpg"},{"ObjectID":4718,"Title":"Seascape with shipping","Artist":"Hagen, Willem van der","Date":"","Medium":"drawing","CreditLine":"The Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge — Paintings, Drawings and Prints","URL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/id/object/4718","ImageURL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/imagestore/pdp/pdp34/PD_397_1963.jpg"},{"ObjectID":47870,"Title":"","Artist":"Unidentified Orvieto pottery","Date":"14th Century","Medium":"tin-glazed earthenware","CreditLine":"The Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge — Applied Arts","URL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/id/object/47870","ImageURL":"https://data.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/imagestore/aa/aa8/C_115_1991_281_29.jpg"},{"ObjectID":49358,"Title":"","Artist":"","Date":"Third Intermediate period","Medium":"funerary equipment","CreditLine":"The Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge — Antiquities","URL":"ht